<html><head><meta http-equiv="Content-Type" content="text/html; charset=utf-8" /><meta http-equiv="Content-Style-Type" content="text/css" /><meta name="generator" content="Aspose.Words for .NET 13.4.0.0" /><title>Written evidence from South Somerset Together (the strategic partnership for South Somerset) (TIC 059)</title></head><body><div><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt; text-align:center"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Written evidence from</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold"> South</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold"> Somerset Together (the strategic partnership for South Somerset)</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">(TIC 059)</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Summary of main </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">points</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">There has been a reduction in local bus services</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> in South Somerset</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> since 2009/10</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">, which has further exacerbated the already difficult transport and accessibility issues in a large rural district.   </span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">There is a need</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">to address the problem of transpor</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">t</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> and accessibility in rural areas such as South Somerset</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> and potential to do so through a different approach</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">.</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">South Somerset Together (SST), the strategic partnership for South Somerset has set up a </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Priority </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Focus Group</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> to tackle the issue.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">This is</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> jointly led by the Yarlington Housing Group (the majority social housing landlord in the district) and SSDC. Membership includes officers </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">of Somerset</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> County Council.</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">The </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Focus Group</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> proposes to set up a pilot to deliver solutions by:-</span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="circle" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><ul type="circle" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Courier New'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 66.2pt; padding-left:5.8pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Taking the service/</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">facility to the people</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> i.e. Delivery of </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">essential </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">services locally to reduce the need and cost of travel and improve community cohesion. </span></li><li style="font-family:'Courier New'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 66.2pt; padding-left:5.8pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Taking the people to the</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">service/facility</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> i.e. Create a </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">local community </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">transport hub linking people together with tra</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">nsport solutions.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span></li></ul><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">T</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">his pilot</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">aims</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> to deliver </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">much improved transport and acces</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">sibility in a very remote area and </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">demonstrate that this type of initiative can deliver better value for money.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">The concept </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">can then be rolled out</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> elsewhere.</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">F</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">unding for such initiatives is an issue, </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">and it is hoped that the government will </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">recognise</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">the specific challenges facing rural transport and will make provision</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">as they have</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">  </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">in urban locations (e.g. Better Bus Areas). </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">                                   </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">                                                                                                                                                                                   </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">                          </span></li></ul><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">1</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">              </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">How do Government and local authorities identif</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">y demand for passenger transport in isolated communities (including rural and urban areas and island communities)?</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">1.1</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">              </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Somerset County Council</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">(</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">SCC</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">)</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> is the Transport Authority for the South Somerset area</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">. However</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">South Somerset Together (SST), the </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">strategic partnership for South Somerset</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">, which includes both SCC and </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">South Somerset District Council (</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">SSDC</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">)</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> along with other key stakeholders, </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">has identified the declining access to services in rural areas as a real barrier for a large variety of resident</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">s</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">.</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">1.2</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">              </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">The SST organised w</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">orkshops in February and April this year</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">, </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">which involved local user groups including Parish C</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">ouncils, service providers (including Citizens Advice, health, housing, education &amp; training and Sport &amp; Leisure), community and public </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">transport providers. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">These workshops </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">established a </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">need (and an ability to provide) for some services to be offered in a more central hub</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">.</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">1.3</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">              </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Additionally </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">the South</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> Somerset Citizens Advice Bureau undertook a survey in January</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> 2013, which indicated that </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">1 in 3 respondents felt that access to employment and healthcare was poor or very poor.</span><a name="_ftnref1"></a><a href="#_ftn1">[1]</a></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">1.4</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">              </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">D</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">etermining actual demand</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> is difficult given the wide</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">dispersal</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">of </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">rural settlements and the varied reasons for travel. What we do know though is that i</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">n contrast</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> to the overall</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> national trend, passenger journeys by bus in Somerset have decreased in the past two years. The county has one of the lowest number of bus trips per population in England.</span><a name="_ftnref2"></a><a href="#_ftn2">[2]</a></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">1.5</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">              </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">The Department for Transport Publ</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">ic Service Vehicle (PSV) Surv</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">ey </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">estimates that in 2011-12, there were 8.6</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> million bus passenger journeys </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">in Somerset.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">T</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">his </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">represents a 12% fall</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> from the</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">2009-10</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> figure of 9.8 million.</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">1.6</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">              </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">T</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">he number of bus journeys per head of population </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">i</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">n </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Somerset has</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> decreased from 18.7 </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">bus </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">journeys</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> per </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">head </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">of population in</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> 2009/10 </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">to 17.9</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> in 2010/11</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> and 16.2 in 2011/12</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">This contrast</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">s with</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> the upward trend in numbers experienced in most local authorities across the South West and in England as a whole.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Somerset has the </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">lowest figure in the </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">South West and </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">one of the</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> lowest </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">in England.</span><a name="_ftnref3"></a><a href="#_ftn3">[3]</a><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> However the </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">neighbouring</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> authorities of Devon and Dorset have </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">also </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">shown a slight downturn since 2010/11. </span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">1.7</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">              </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Whilst it is difficult to ascertain an exact correlation it is likely that this decrease in patron</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">age has arisen due to the reductions in local bus subsidy during the same time frame. Additionally the drop in</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> the</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">reimburs</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">ement rate to the operators for </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">concessionary fares from 70% to 55% is likely to have had a greater impact on rural bus routes where,</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> unlike urban areas, there is considerably  less opportunity to generate any additional patronage through the free-fare scheme. It is also likely that the Government’s 20% reduction in Bus Service Operator’s grant may well have had a more adverse </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">impact </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">on</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> rural routes</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">.</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">1.8</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">              </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">The net result is that many marginal rural routes have either been withdrawn or curtailed. Across the</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> whole</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> District there are now no evening bus routes</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> after around 6/7pm, </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">and only two infrequent routes remain in operation on a Sunday.</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">1.9</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">              </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">The</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> Focus</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> Group</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> recognises </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">that it is n</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">o longer</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> possible to continue to subsidise</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> bus</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> routes where there is little potential of </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">achieving a</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> realistic degree of viability and </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">hence the need for a different approach.</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">2</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">              </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">To what extent are the needs of </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">different groups of passengers (e.g. people with disabilities, older people, young people) taken into account in determining the provision of public tra</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">nsport to isolated communities?</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">2.1</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">              </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Lack of access to transport is a huge issue for many people living </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">in rural areas. For those families where there is only one</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">, or no</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">, vehicle</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> and/or limited public transport, it can restrict access to key services such as healthcare</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">, education, social activities,</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> etc. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">This particularly impacts on women especially with you</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">ng children.  </span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">2.2</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">              </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Access to support groups for those facing discrimination or other challenges is much more difficult as the groups tend to operate within the larger towns. This particularly impacts on the LGBT community and those with disabilities includ</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">ing people with mental health challenges and those experiencing domestic violence or other forms of harassment.</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">2.3</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">              </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Living in rural areas poses particular challenges for people with disabilities in accessing education, training, and employment opportunitie</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">s and playing an active role in their communities. Access to transport is crucial and voluntary sector provision or adapted taxis are often very expensive.</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">2.4</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">              </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Evidence shows considerable variability in the provision and availability of services between di</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">fferent rural </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">areas but</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> overall, the picture is of under-provision and they are less likely to receive services comparable with their urban counterparts.</span><a name="_ftnref4"></a><a href="#_ftn4">[4]</a><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> For example, older people in rural areas are likely to receive lower levels of supportive services su</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">ch as domiciliary care and meals on wheels than those living in urban areas, and the general take-up rates for welfare benefits seem lower.</span></p><p style="background-color:#ffffff; line-height:12.45pt; margin:5pt 0pt 7.5pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">2.5</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">              </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Young people are also significantly </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">disadvantaged</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">: whilst they are taken into account where there is a statutory</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> requirement e</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">g</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> getting people to school, there is no provision to allow young people to take part in </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">extracurricular</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> activities and other social networking as they can’t get home afterwards or </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">travel at weekends.  This also impacts on their ability to take part in further training and job search and limits employment opportunities to those accessible by public transport which significantly reduces their opportunities. </span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">3</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">              </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">What are the main chall</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">enges associated with providing better and more consistent bus and rail services to isolated communities? How can these challenges be overcome</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">?</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">3.1</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">              </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">T</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">he cost of </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">rail </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">infrastructure</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> means t</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">hat it is not</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> cost effective </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">where </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">the settlements are </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">not </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">within th</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">e catchment area for existing routes. In South Somerset there is some potential on the Bristol – Weymouth line if appropriate arrival and departure times were provided at </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">stations in the district and a business case establishing the viability of improved t</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">imetabling has been undertaken on behalf of the Community Rail Partnership.</span><a name="_ftnref5"></a><a href="#_ftn5">[5]</a><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">3.2</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">              </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">The b</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">us </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">offers</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> more flexible</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> options</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">,</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> but with major reductions in recent years to the subsidised bus network and the unlikelihood that commercial services will be viable to take their place, the overall bus network of routes has significantly reduced especially in rural areas.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">H</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">istorically t</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">he temptation when passenger numbers have dwindled has often been to merge </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">routes</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">, however long end to end journey times are often a significant deterrent to travel except for those that have no other alternative</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">. Whilst this may achieve a short term savin</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">g in subsidy costs the net result is often a long and circuitous route and consequently further dwindling numbers.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">  </span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">3.3</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">              </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">A more proactive approach would be </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">to develop more community based transport groups such as small parish car schemes or DRT type servi</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">ces that feed into the main arterial commercial bus routes</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">. Lincolnshire CC has adopted this type of approach</span><a name="_ftnref6"></a><a href="#_ftn6">[6]</a><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">.</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">3.4</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">              </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">See also, our answer to the following question.</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">4</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">              </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">How effectively do Community Transport services address the needs of passengers in </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">isolated communities? How could Community Transport be improved?</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">4.1</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">              </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Community Transport </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">can be very effective</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> in delivering transport to isolated communities.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">They</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> have local knowledge,</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> both of the area and their</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> customer</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">s. They can offer a bespoke servi</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">ce often door-to-door for those in most need.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">H</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">owever costs </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">to</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> the passenger</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">,</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> funding and resource availability for the operator can be major issues. </span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">4.2</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">              </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Further issues arise with the lack of communication and coordination between all transport groups with operators working in isolation of each </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">other. At</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> best this can result in unintentional duplication and at worse a complete failure for </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">someone to make a </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">journey</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> at their convenience, and thus</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">there is potential to improve service delivery through closer partnership working </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">between</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> the transport operators</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">.</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">4.3</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">              </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">A lack of good transport information can also be a problem for local residents, who often don’t k</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">now what services are available to them even where they exist.  Therefore a comprehensive access point where accurate information can be sourced would improve access to community transport.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">4.4</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">              </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">The SST workshops held earlier this year established that</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">t</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">ransport in itself </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">may </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">not</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> be</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> the whole solution </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">and that </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">a mixture of </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">strategies to include providing</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> services</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> more locally needed to be considered.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> The partnership proposes to set up a pilot to deliver the solutions</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> as set out</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> below:-</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 39.01pt; padding-left:2.99pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Take the service/f</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">acility to the people</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> i.e. Delivery of services locally to reduce the need and cost of travel and improve community cohesion. </span></li><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 39.01pt; padding-left:2.99pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Take the people to the</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">service/facility</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> i.e. Create a transport hub linking people together with transport solutions.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 24pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">4.5</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">              </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">The ma</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">in purpose is to trial an innovative project to mitigate rural isolation and improve access to essential services through the creation of a community hub. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">This hub is likely to be the accepted market town for the area with a number of locations within it p</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">roviding a set of accessible services. These may or may not be co-located depending on natural affinities</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">SST has identified a number of services that could be delivered more locally, such as Health Clinics, Further Education and Training, Citizens Advice Bureau and Community/Social Housing services.  </span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">4.6</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">              </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">The SST will work with the District and County Council</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">s, health and education partners, community facilitators and housing associations to develop a local community package of services that could be provided through this community hub.  </span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">4.7</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">              </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">A Community Transport scheme</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> will act as the catalyst providing affo</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">rdable transport links to the hub.  Alongside this partners will work with bus operators and community transport groups (including potential community car schemes) to develop an integrated transport infrastructure and a transport hub. Besides increasing ac</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">cessibility it also offers an opportunity to gain additional patronage on the</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> existing</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> core </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">bus</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> and coach</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> services serving </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">the hub</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">.</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">4.8</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">              </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">The hub will become a one-stop shop for transport solutions</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> in that area</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">, providing information, booking services and de</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">livery through public bus, car schemes, car sharing and community transport.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> Beneficiaries from such a scheme:</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:18pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold">4.8.1</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold">              </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold">Residents would benefit from: </span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">A one-stop-shop with targeted transport and community information; delivered through the hub and a </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">website.</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">A more joined up and accessible network of transport enabling greater convenience to access services, greater opportunities and independence to individuals who may otherwise be rurally isolated.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Reduced cost of travel.</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Improved training and work</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> opportunities; training courses will be delivered within the community, for the community.</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Greener environment; the better utilisation of local transport resources coupled with delivering services locally will reduce the need for individuals to travel lon</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">g distances.</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Investment in local area and businesses; improving the local transport network and providing a hub for community activity are likely to encourage trade for local businesses. </span></li></ul><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:18pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold">4.8.2</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold">              </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold">Transport operators would</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold"> benefit from:</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Increased patronage on</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> existing routes delivering greater productivity.</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Greater potential for interchange with other routes/operators.</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Improved rapport between public and community transport leading to better understanding as to how respective services can compliment.</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Opportuni</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">ties to enhance the relationship with the wider community presenting increased opportunities to meet the needs of potential new customers.</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Goodwill – being seen to be doing ‘the right thing’</span></li></ul><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:18pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold">4.8.3</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold">              </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold">Community Service</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold"> Providers would</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold"> benefit from:</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Reduced cos</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">ts by sharing facilities and travel arrangements with other providers.</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Higher proportion of appointments (both pre-arranged &amp; desirable) occurring.</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Increased awareness of the local ‘on the ground’ situation.</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Improved understanding of the issues faced by ot</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">her service providers increasing the opportunities for even closer liaison and further savings.</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Enhanced empathy with their clients/customers.</span></li></ul><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">5</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">              </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">To what extent should passengers in isolated communities be expected to rely on taxis and other </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">demand-responsive transport services?</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">5.1</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">              </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">There is, at least initially, a resistance to advance booking the service for any demand responsive or taxi-bus type service, although this can generally be overcome by better education and raising awareness</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Cost of travel for the passenger can be a major issue, especially for those on low incomes and fixed pensions. Very often (as has been highlighted in the</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> 2012</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> OFT </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">consultation)</span><a name="_ftnref7"></a><a href="#_ftn7">[7]</a><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> those in rural communities pay a higher proportion of their income on transpor</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">t. </span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">5.2</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">              </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">There</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> is </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">also </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">the disparity that often arises </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">in respect of</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> the ability to </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">use a bus pass. Whilst</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> the County Councils have discretionary powers to extend the bus pass scheme to include CT schemes, often budgetary constraints means that this doesn’</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">t happen or as in Somerset it is offered at reduced rate (50%) with a cap fares for longer journeys (currently £10 in Somerset).  I</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">n theory it is possible for taxi operators to register a ‘ta</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">xi bus service’ under the 1985 T</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">ransport</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> Act</span><a name="_ftnref8"></a><a href="#_ftn8">[8]</a><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> and similarly the l</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">arger Community Transport operators can register a local bus route either under</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> section 22</span><a name="_ftnref9"></a><a href="#_ftn9">[9]</a><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> or a Public Service Vehicle Operator’s licence</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">. I</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">n more remote areas the small community transport </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">and</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> small taxi operators have been very reluctant to do this. Oft</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">en they do not have the resources, skills or funds to undertake what they see as a very bureaucratic process</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Similarly many</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> remote</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> areas are served by community car schemes, which</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> rely on direct payment to the driver to cover costs (usually 45ppm recognised by HM Revenue &amp; Customs). </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">The net result, where such small </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">schemes do evolve</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">,</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> is passengers have to pay often quite high fares where their urban counterparts can travel for free</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">6</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">              </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">What are the main challenges associated with funding transport services in isolated communities? How can these services be made more affordable?</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">6.1</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">              </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">The main challenge is to overcome the “we’ve always done it this way approach”</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> to the provision of</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> rural transport. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Whilst the economic downturn has resulted in a relatively rapid withdrawal of financial support for bus services that had previously seen escalating costs, with little potential for passenger growth; little has been done</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> to date</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> either in</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> South Somerset or nationally to look at options that can mitigate the impact</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> of local bus service provision</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> often for those groups with the most need. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> The concept that we have outlined above </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">offers a potential solution to this issue. </span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">6.2</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">              </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">The low </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">population density in most of these areas means</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> that the cost per passenger is likely to be high when compared with </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">most</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> urban routes. As </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">indicated</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> above </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">typically all types of Community Transport schemes have evolved on an ad hoc basis to meet </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">the needs o</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">f their community,</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> often in response to the decline or withdrawal of local bus services. Laudable as this is their very nature means they often operate in isolation from each other and </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">public transport operators. Closer liaison</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> means that savings could</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> oft</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">en</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> be</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> made by the</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> CT</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> operators and</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> with the added potential of increasing patronage on core routes.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">6.3</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">              </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">There is a need to address the disparity between urban and rural areas in respect of the bus pass</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">. One option (that’s currently not permitted under th</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">e </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Concessionary Fare Scheme)</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> that we often encounter in feedback from the community is that </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">a small flat fare could be levied for bus pass use. The monies raised </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">could then be used to extend the scheme.</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">6.4</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">              </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Additionally the government has made specific pu</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">blic transport funding available through grant schemes. These</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> have</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> primarily</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">been </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">targeted at</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">urban</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> areas (</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">e.g.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> Better Bus </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Area</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> &amp; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">the Green Bus Fund</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">)</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">.</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="background-color:#ffffff; line-height:12.45pt; margin:0pt 0pt 7.5pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">6.5</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">              </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">There is also a </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">need to</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> develop services that people will use – ie they go where they need to go when people want them to.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> We need to get more flexibility from agencies and services that people go </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">to make</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> it easier.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> For example, more ability to pick appointments in hospitals; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">grouping services so that in one trip to town, someone can achieve lots of tasks.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> We also need agencies like DWP to be more flexible and innovative – for example, using on line tools to verify claimants’ work search; using housing providers or district co</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">uncil offices to hold Job Centre services rather than expecting those on benefit to travel to the larger towns.</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">September 2013</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:11.5pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11.5pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p></div><hr style="width:33%; height:1px; text-align:left" /><p style="margin:0pt"><a name="_ftn1"></a><a href="#_ftnref1">[1]</a><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> Transport and the Accessibility of Public Services Report - </span><span style="font-family:Helvetica; font-size:10pt">South </span><span style="font-family:Helvetica; font-size:10pt">Somerset Citizens Advi</span><span style="font-family:Helvetica; font-size:10pt">ce Bureau</span><span style="font-family:Helvetica; font-size:10pt"> January 2013</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><a name="_ftn2"></a><a href="#_ftnref2">[2]</a><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> SCC’s </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">Transport Statistics for Somerset – </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">August </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">2013 update</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><a name="_ftn3"></a><a href="#_ftnref3">[3]</a><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> DfT Table BUS0110a Passenger journeys on local bus services per head by local authority1,2: England, from 2009/10</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">              </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">              </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">              </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">              </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">              </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">              </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">              </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">              </span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><a name="_ftn4"></a><a href="#_ftnref4">[4]</a><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">Obstacles to Using and</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> Providing Rural Social Care</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> - </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">Social Care Institute for Excellence</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> – September 2007</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><a name="_ftn5"></a><a href="#_ftnref5">[5]</a><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> The Heart of Wessex Line – Case for Service Improvement – Image rail November 2011</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><a name="_ftn6"></a><a href="#_ftnref6">[6]</a><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> Lincs </span><span style="font-family:Arial; 